@DATABASE TagList V1.00
$VER: PureBasic - TagList library V1.00 (01.09.1999) © Fantaisie Software
@NODE MAIN "TagList V1.00"

  @{b}PureBasic TagList library V1.00@{ub}

    Taglists are widely used in the PureBasic libraries and in the
    AmigaOS. It's simply a way to supply a list of paramaters to a
    functions. You can have any parameters you want in any order so
    it's very flexible. These functions simplify to the max the use
    of taglists, so I hope you will not have any problems with them.

  @{b}Commands summary:@{ub}

    @{" AddTag        " LINK AddTag}
    @{" ChangeTag     " LINK ChangeTag}
    @{" FreeTagList   " LINK FreeTagList}
    @{" InitTagList   " LINK InitTagList}
    @{" ResetTagList  " LINK ResetTagList}
    @{" TagListID     " LINK TagListID}

@ENDNODE


@NODE AddTag

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  AddTag(#TAG_ITEM, #TAG_DATA)

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  Add the given tags to the taglist.

@ENDNODE


@NODE ChangeTag

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  ChangeTag(Position, #TAG_ITEM, #TAG_DATA)

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  Change the tag value at the given position in the current TagList

@ENDNODE


@NODE FreeTagList

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  FreeTagList()

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  Frees the memory allocated by InitTagList(). After this you CAN'T
  use the TagList functions any more, you must recall InitTagList()
  if you need to build a taglist.

@ENDNODE


@NODE InitTagList

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  TagList.l = InitTagList(#NumMaxTags)

    @{b}COMMAND@{ub}
  Init all the TagList environments for later use. You must put this
  function at the top of your source code if you want to use the TagList
  commands. This command allocates a memory zone of (#NumMaxTags+2)*8 bytes.
  It returns the memory start address or 0 if it can't allocate the memory
  (should never happen). You can free this memory when you don't need to
  use the TagList any more with the FreeTagList() command.

@ENDNODE


@NODE ResetTagList

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  ResetTagList(#TAG_ITEM, #TAG_DATA)

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  Rebuild a new taglist from scratch and put the given tag inside.

@ENDNODE


@NODE TagListID

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  TagList.l = TagListID()

    @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
  Returns the TagList pointer for passing to any command requiring the
  taglist (Window(), Screen(), ASL(), etc.)

@ENDNODE


